            </a>
        <p><br>A camber snowboard is in a shape of a frowny face when looked at from the side. It is a great bard to use
            on all types of runs. A camber board will pop out of deeper snow well. They will give a better pop for larger
            jumps. They are great for  turning at higher speeds. A camber board is more difficult to manuver at slower
            speeds. They are a bit more difficult to manage the jib park as well.</p>
    </div>
